This is only interesting to like 48 year olds, but per Dr. Ray Peat taking Potassium Bicarbonate is insanely effective at reducing high blood pressure, just have to be careful to keep it at low dosages to not "relax" the heart too much. No one here will care but commit to memory.

Ray Peat said on a radio show that some balneology study discovered the organism's affinity for CO2 is so high that it basically flows in through the skin. Paracelsus was the doctor who invented/revived the concept of natural mineral springs baths being good. So credit is due.

Another fun fact from same show, but apparently baking soda potentiates skin permeability for Magnesium, so if put both Magnesium and baking soda in the bath tub, you're basically getting more bang for your buck. Like 1-2 pounds of baking soda, big dosage can be used for bathing.
